<metal:block use-macro="main_template">

  <div metal:fill-slot="content">
    
    <div class="intro-block">
      <h1>Please ask for registration</h1>
      This is a demo installation of Phoenix. If you want to try it out please do the following steps:
      <ol>
        <li>
          Get an OpenID Account at an ESGF Node, 
          for example at <a href="http://esgf-data.dkrz.de">http://esgf-data.dkrz.de</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          To be allowed to download data from ESGF (e.a. CORDEX) you
          must be registered in the <b>non-commercial</b> ESGF
          Group. You can register for this group by just downloading data
          files from an <a href="http://esgf-data.dkrz.de">ESGF Node</a>. 
          When you are not registered you will be asked for group registration once.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="btn btn-mini btn-success" href="${request.route_path('account_login', protocol='oauth2')}">Sign in</a> with your OpenID at Phoenix.
        </li>
        <li>
          You will only have <b>guest</b> status and an admin needs to activate your account.
        </li>
        <li>
          We will inform you when you are added to the allowed users of this Demo.
        </li>
        <li>
          Finally login again with your OpenID.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    
  </div>

</metal:block>

